  "title": "Technician (Heat Treatment, Aerospace)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Operate vacuum furnaces for heat treatment and brazing processes to ensure proper function.</li>\n  <li>Perform SAT, uniformity checks, and leak rate tests on vacuum furnaces.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and address any abnormal conditions in both parts and furnaces, taking appropriate corrective actions.</li>\n  <li>Conduct incoming inspections on parts before heat treatment and perform TPM checks on equipment.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate records for heat treatment logs and furnace operations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>At least 2 years of relevant experience in the<strong> Aerospace Industry.</strong></li>\n  <li>Able to interpret operational documents and follow complex instructions.</li>\n  <li>Strong attention to detail, multitasking abilities, and commitment to safety protocols.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
